tion": ["Returns a {class}`SourcePosition` instance, describing the position of\nthis token's first character in the source.\n"]}, {"name": "rply.token.Token.getstr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the string represented by this token."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Represents a syntactically relevant piece of text.\n\n```\nparam name\n\nA string describing the kind of text represented.\n\nparam value\n\nThe actual text represented.\n\nparam source_pos\n\nA  object representing the\nposition of the first character in the source from which\nthis token was generated.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "rply.token.SourcePosition", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "rply.token.SourcePosition.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "idx", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lineno", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "colno", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rply.token.SourcePosition.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Represents the position of a character in some source string.\n\n```\nparam idx\n\nThe index of the character in the source.\n\nparam lineno\n\nThe number of the line in which the character occurs.\n\nparam colno\n\nThe number of the column in which the character occurs.\n```\n\nThe values passed to this object can be retrieved using the identically\nnamed attributes.\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "rply.parser", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "rply.parser.LRParser", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "rply.parser.LRParser.__init__", "asynchronous"