ous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tokens", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "precedence", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "cache_id", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.production", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "rule", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "precedence", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["A decorator that defines one or many production rules and registers\nthe decorated function to be called with the terminals and\nnon-terminals matched by those rules.\n\nA `rule` should consist of a name defining the non-terminal returned\nby the decorated function and one or more sequences of pipe-separated\nnon-terminals and terminals that are supposed to be replaced:\n\n```\nreplacing_non_terminal : TERMINAL1 non_term1 | TERMINAL2 non_term2\n```\n\nThe name of the non-terminal replacing the sequence is on the left,\nseparated from the sequence by a colon. The whitespace around the colon\nis required.\n\nKnowing this we can define productions:\n\n```\npg = ParserGenerator(['NUMBER', 'ADD'])\n\n@pg.production('number : NUMBER')\ndef expr_number(p):\n    return BoxInt(int(p[0].getstr()))\n\n@pg.production('expr : number ADD number')\ndef expr_add(p):\n    return BoxInt(p[0].getint() + p[2].getint())\n```\n\nIf a state was passed to the parser, the decorated function is\nadditionally called with that state as first argument.\n"]}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Sets the error handler that is called with the state (if passed to the\nparser) and the token the parser errored on.\n\nCurrently error handlers must raise an exception. If an error handler\nis not defined, a {exc}`rply.ParsingError` will be raised.\n"]}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.compute_grammar_hash", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "g", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.serialize_table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "table", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.data_is_valid", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "g", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.build", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator._write_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache_dir", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cache_file", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "table", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "rply.parsergenerator.ParserGenerator.VERSION", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A ParserGenerator represents a set of production rules, that define a\nsequence of terminals and non-terminals to be replaced with a non-terminal,\nwhich can be turned into a parser.\n\n```\nparam tokens\n\nA list of token (non-terminal) names.\n\nparam precedence\n\nA list of tuples defining the order of operation for\navoiding ambiguity, consisting of a string defining\nassociativity (left, right or nonassoc) and a list of\ntoken names with the sam